# Vitest Usage in Tests

## Description
This rule defines the proper usage of Vitest functions and utilities in test files.

## Requirements
- Use global Vitest functions without importing them
- Only import specific utilities that aren't globally available
- Use proper test organization with describe blocks
- Follow Arrange-Act-Assert pattern
- Use descriptive test names

## Examples
```typescript
// ✅ Correct usage
describe('MyService', () => {
  beforeEach(() => {
    // setup
  })
  
  it('should return 404 when resource is not found', () => {
    // Arrange
    const service = new MyService()
    
    // Act
    const result = service.getResource('non-existent')
    
    // Assert
    expect(result.status).toBe(404)
  })
})

// ❌ Incorrect usage
import { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest' // Don't import global functions
```

## Error Prevention
- Use Biome rules to prevent importing global Vitest functions
- Use TypeScript to ensure proper typing of test assertions
- Use descriptive test names to make failures more understandable

